// bisect: JIT codegen bug (same class as 01, borrowed-inner variant)
// interp/jit: both return [i64:2, i64:3] post-fix.
// root_cause: same representation confusion as 01, via the BORROWED
// path — the qop inner is a Local read of a Nullable local, so the
// pre-fix arm called graphix_valarray_clone(payload), dereferencing the
// in-Value ValArray bits as a `*const ValArray`. Post-fix this routes
// through graphix_value_into_array_borrowed (clones the inner, forgets
// the input; the env slot's scope-exit drop balances).
{ let a = [i64:1, i64:2, i64:3]; let x = a[1..]; x$ }
